# Ollama Modelfile for the fine-tuned CyberSentry model.
#
# Usage:
#   1. Place your GGUF file (e.g. model-q3-k-m.gguf) in this directory,
#      or update the FROM path below to point at it.
#   2. Run: ollama create cybersentry -f Modelfile
#   3. Test: ollama run cybersentry "What is CVE-2024-3400?"
#
# NOTE: Ollama's library already ships a "qwen3" base template that
# includes Hermes-style tool-calling support. If your GGUF was exported
# with Qwen3's tokenizer_config.json chat_template intact, Ollama will
# usually pick it up automatically and you may not need the TEMPLATE
# block below at all -- try without it first, and only add it if tool
# calls show up as raw text in the response `content` instead of the
# structured `tool_calls` field.

FROM ./model-q3-k-m.gguf

PARAMETER temperature 0.2
PARAMETER num_ctx 8192

SYSTEM """You are CyberSentry, a defensive cybersecurity analysis assistant."""
